---
import PresentationLayout from '~/layouts/PresentationLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Agentic Coding: Scaling with Agent Swarms',
  description: 'Using agent swarms for codebase analysis and mass refactoring at scale.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: false,
};
---

<PresentationLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Slide 1: Title -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1>Agentic Coding</h1>
    <h2>Scaling with Agent Swarms</h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 2: About Me -->
  <section>
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <div
      style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 80%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"
    >
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🛠️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">15 years of software engineering experience</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">❤️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">I genuinely enjoy coding and building software</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🏗️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Currently building <strong>Agewise</strong> as CTO</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🤖</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Me and my team delegate <strong>99% of coding</strong> to AI agents</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 3: Agenda -->
  <section>
    <h2>Agenda</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The Context Window Problem</li>
      <li>Project Analysis with Agent Swarms</li>
      <li>Mass Refactoring with Agent Swarms</li>
      <li>A Real-World Migration Story</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 4: The Problem -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Context Window Problem</h2>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8;">
        Working on a single feature, module, or bug? One agent handles it fine.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        But what if you need to <strong>analyze the entire codebase</strong>?<br />
        Read every test file. Map all dependencies. Understand how 13 factories connect to 136 tests.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        One context window isn't enough.<br />
        Precision drops when you force everything into a single session.
      </p>
      <div
        style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 2.5rem;"
      >
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
          It's like trying to read <strong>10 books at once</strong> — you can hold them all, but you won't remember the
          details.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 5: Running Example -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Running Example</h2>
    <div
      style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 2rem;"
    >
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #0ea5c1;">Test Data Factory Migration</h3>
      <ul style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        <li>Test factories creating data through API endpoints</li>
        <li>Problem: can't test data not created via endpoints + API overhead</li>
        <li>Decision: migrate to use services directly</li>
      </ul>
      <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">
        <p style="font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 0;">
          13 factories. 136 test files. One engineer. One afternoon.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 2: Project Analysis ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 6: Section Header -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.2rem;">Project Analysis with Agent Swarms</h1>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem;">
      Before you change anything, understand what you're dealing with.
    </h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 7: Naive vs Swarm -->
  <section>
    <h2>Single Agent vs. Swarm</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #ef4444; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #ef4444;">Naive Approach</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <li>Ask Claude to analyze everything at once</li>
          <li>Context gets diluted</li>
          <li>Accuracy drops on details</li>
          <li>Findings are incomplete</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #4ade80;">Swarm Approach</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <li>Divide the codebase into subsets</li>
          <li>Each agent analyzes a focused slice</li>
          <li>Findings are precise and complete</li>
          <li>Results converge into a summary</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 8: The Swarm Analysis Pattern -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Swarm Analysis Pattern</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <!-- Orchestrator -->
      <div
        style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 0.75rem 2rem; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem;"
      >
        Main Agent — defines scope
      </div>
      <!-- Arrow down -->
      <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #0ea5c1;">↓ spawns N sub-agents</div>
      <!-- Sub-agents -->
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 0.75rem; width: 100%;">
        <div
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;"
        >
          Agent 1<br /><span style="color: #a0aec0;">Module A</span>
        </div>
        <div
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;"
        >
          Agent 2<br /><span style="color: #a0aec0;">Module B</span>
        </div>
        <div
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;"
        >
          Agent 3<br /><span style="color: #a0aec0;">Module C</span>
        </div>
        <div
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;"
        >
          Agent N<br /><span style="color: #a0aec0;">Module D</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Arrow down -->
      <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #0ea5c1;">↓ findings converge</div>
      <!-- Summary -->
      <div
        style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.15); border: 2px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 10px; padding: 0.75rem 2rem; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem;"
      >
        Structured Summary
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align: center; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
      Each agent analyzes a group of factories — what it creates, which endpoints it calls, which tests depend on it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 9: How to Launch a Swarm -->
  <section>
    <h2>How Do You Launch a Swarm?</h2>
    <p style="margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: #a0aec0;">
      You just describe what you want. The agent figures out the rest.
    </p>
    <div
      style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.08); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; text-align: left; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #e2e8f0;"
    >
      <span style="color: #a0aec0;">$</span> Look into <span style="color: #0ea5c1;">src/tests/</span> directory.<br />
      Find all test files.<br />
      For each test file, <span style="color: #0ea5c1;">run a Haiku sub-agent</span> that analyzes the test<br />
      and explains the steps taken in each test case.<br /><br />
      As the result I want a <span style="color: #4ade80;">report about the module's test coverage</span><br />
      so I can share it with our QA lead.
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        That's it. The main agent reads the directory, spawns sub-agents, collects results, and writes the report.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 10: Practical Tips -->
  <section>
    <h2>Practical Tips for Analysis Swarms</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚡</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Use Haiku for sub-agents</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Fast, cheap, and more than sufficient for read-only analysis work</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">✂️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Divide the work upfront</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Split the scope yourself or ask the main agent to help distribute it across sub-agents</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎯</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Orchestrator orchestrates, doesn't code</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            The main agent distributes work and collects results. Sub-agents do the actual analysis.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        I'm on the <strong>$100/month subscription</strong>. Running 10 Haiku agents for analysis — you don't even feel
        it. It's not noticeable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 3: Mass Refactoring ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 10: Section Header -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.2rem;">Mass Refactoring with Agent Swarms</h1>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem;">
      Build one perfect example. Let agents replicate the pattern.
    </h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 11: Tests Are Non-Negotiable -->
  <section>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem;">
      <blockquote
        style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 600; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0; line-height: 1.4; max-width: 90%;"
      >
        "Refactoring without automated tests is gambling.<br />With or without AI."
      </blockquote>
      <div style="margin-top: 3rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; max-width: 80%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0;">
          Tests are a <strong>prerequisite</strong>, not a nice-to-have.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0;">
          Both you and AI will miss details without automation.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #e2e8f0; margin: 0;">
          This applies whether a human or Claude does the refactoring.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 12: The Golden Reference -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Golden Reference</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎯</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Know your destination</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Before mass refactoring, you need to know exactly what the result looks like</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔨</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Refactor ONE unit first</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Invest the time. Do it manually or with your main agent. Make it good.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🤖</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Replicate golden example</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">This is where AI shines — replicating a known, proven pattern across many targets</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        The first factory migration took <strong>1 hour</strong>. After that, I knew exactly what the target looked like.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 13: The Learnings Document -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Learnings Document</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #4ade80;">Consistent Targets</h3>
        <p style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          If all targets follow the same pattern — you may not need a document at all. The golden reference is enough.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #f0c36d;">Targets with Variation</h3>
        <p style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          Edge cases, different behaviors? Create a learnings document. Capture patterns, tricky spots, exceptions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📝</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Give it to agents as instructions</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            After each iteration, add new learnings you discover. Each iteration gets smarter.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Too much variation? <strong>Split into phases.</strong> Categorize targets first, then mass-refactor category by
        category.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 14: Executing the Refactoring -->
  <section>
    <h2>Executing the Refactoring</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >1</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Use <strong>Haiku sub-agents</strong> to discover and list all targets</p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >2</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">
          Split targets across <strong>N Sonnet agents</strong> — main agent distributes the work
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #0ea5c1; color: white; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >3</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Execute in parallel — each agent handles its batch</p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); border: 1px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: #4ade80; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"
          >4</span
        >
        <p style="margin: 0;">Verify batch: <strong>run tests → review → adjust → commit</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        12 remaining factories + 136 test files, module by module, <strong>~4 hours including review</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 15: The Review Problem -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Review Problem</h2>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8;">
        Mass refactoring = many changes.<br />
        <strong>All of it needs to be reviewed.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 3px solid #ef4444; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1); margin-top: 2rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem;">
        The temptation: offload everything to agents and make a <strong>leap of faith</strong>.<br />
        But this is about <strong>giving up control</strong> — the opposite of what we want.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 2rem; text-align: center;">
      <div
        style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #e2e8f0;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px;"
          >Refactor</span
        >
        <span style="color: #0ea5c1;">→</span>
        <span
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px;"
          >Review</span
        >
        <span style="color: #0ea5c1;">→</span>
        <span
          style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); border: 1px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px;"
          >Adjust</span
        >
        <span style="color: #0ea5c1;">→</span>
        <span
          style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.2); border: 1px solid #4ade80; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px;"
          >Commit</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 2rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        You already get <strong>enormous speed</strong>. Don't be greedy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 16: Handling Complexity -->
  <section>
    <h2>Handling Complexity</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📊</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Categorize first</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Use Haiku to classify targets by complexity before executing anything</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚡</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Batch the simple ones</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Mass-refactor the straightforward targets in parallel</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔍</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Complex cases — one by one</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            The speed is already very high even one-by-one. Don't batch what isn't safe to batch.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); margin-top: 1.25rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        After each complex case, add learnings to your document for the next one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 17: When Things Go Wrong -->
  <section>
    <h2>When Things Go Wrong</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🧪</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Tests are your first line of defense</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Run tests after each batch, not after all batches</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔬</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Isolate failures</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">If a batch fails: isolate the failing targets, re-run individually</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔄</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Version control is your safety net</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Commit after each successful batch — always have a clean rollback point</p>
        </div>
      </div>
