  <!-- Slide 20: Key Principles -->
  <section>
    <h2>Key Principles</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: 1.25rem;">
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">1.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <strong>Divide and conquer</strong> — don't cram a large codebase into one context
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">2.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <strong>Build the golden reference</strong> before going wide
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">3.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <strong>Capture learnings</strong> when targets vary — each iteration feeds the next
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">4.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <strong>Classify complexity</strong> before executing — not everything is simple
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">5.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <strong>Automated tests</strong> are your prerequisite, not your safety net
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">6.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
          <strong>Review every batch</strong> — don't make a leap of faith
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #0ea5c1; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.05); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;"
      >
        <span style="font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; min-width: 1.5rem;">7.</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
